   "source": [
    "# Value Iteration Tutorial\n",
    "\n",
    "[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/dgaida/adversarial2dEnvAI/blob/master/notebooks/Value_Iteration.ipynb)\n",
    "\n",
    "In diesem Notebook lernen wir den **Value Iteration** Algorithmus kennen, einen klassischen Dynamic Programming Ansatz im Reinforcement Learning. Wir nutzen ihn, um eine optimale Strategie (Policy) für unseren Agenten im `CustomGrid` Environment zu finden."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "Zuerst installieren wir das Package und bereiten die Umgebung vor."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install git+https://github.com/dgaida/adversarial2dEnvAI.git\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from custom_grid_env.interface import AgentInterface\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set dummy video driver for headless environment\n",
    "os.environ[\"SDL_VIDEODRIVER\"] = \"dummy\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Der Algorithmus: Value Iteration\n",
    "\n",
    "Value Iteration basiert auf der Bellman-Optimaleitätsgleichung:\n",
    "\n",
    "3237V_{k+1}(s) = \max_{a} \sum_{s', r} p(s', r | s, a) [r + \gamma V_k(s')]3237\n",
    "\n",
    "In unserem deterministischen Fall (ohne Slip) vereinfacht sich dies zu:\n",
    "3237V(s) = \max_{a} [r(s, a) + \gamma V(s')] \3237\n",
    "\n",
    "Wir iterieren über alle Zustände, bis die Werte konvergieren."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def value_iteration(env, goal_pos, gamma=0.9, theta=1e-4):\n",
    "    rows, cols = env.rows, env.cols\n",
    "    V = np.zeros((rows, cols))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    while True:\n",
    "        delta = 0\n",
    "        for r in range(rows):\n",
    "            for c in range(cols):\n",
    "                if (r, c) == goal_pos:\n",
    "                    continue\n",
    "                \n",
    "                v_old = V[r, c]\n",
    "                q_values = []\n",
    "                \n",
    "                for action in range(4): # 0:L, 1:D, 2:R, 3:U\n",
    "                    # Simuliere Bewegung (interner Helper)\n",
    "                    next_pos = env._move_entity([r, c], action)\n",
    "                    \n",
    "                    # Reward-Struktur\n",
    "                    reward = -1.0\n",
    "                    if tuple(next_pos) == goal_pos:\n",
    "                        reward = 100.0\n",
    "                    \n",
    "                    q_values.append(reward + gamma * V[next_pos[0], next_pos[1]])\n",
    "                \n",
    "                V[r, c] = max(q_values)\n",
    "                delta = max(delta, abs(v_old - V[r, c]))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if delta < theta:\n",
    "            break\n",
    "            \n",
    "    return V"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Training und Visualisierung\n",
    "\n",
    "Wir lassen den Algorithmus auf das Standard-Grid los."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "interface = AgentInterface(render=True, render_mode=\"rgb_array\")\n",
    "env = interface.env\n",
    "goal_pos = (3, 4)\n",
    "\n",
    "V = value_iteration(env, goal_pos)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "plt.imshow(V, cmap='viridis')\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='State Value (V)')\n",
    "plt.title(\"Value Function V(s)\")\n",
    "for r in range(env.rows):\n",
    "    for c in range(env.cols):\n",
    "        plt.text(c, r, f\"{V[r, c]:.1f}\", ha=\"center\", va=\"center\", color=\"white\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Ausführung der Optimalen Policy\n",
    "\n",
    "Die optimale Aktion in jedem Zustand ist diejenige, die den Erwartungswert maximiert."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "obs = interface.reset()\n",
    "done = False\n",
    "steps = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "while not done and steps < 20:\n",
    "    current_pos = tuple(env.agent_pos)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Finde beste Aktion basierend auf V\n",
    "    action_values = []\n",
    "    for a in range(4):\n",
    "        next_pos = env._move_entity(list(current_pos), a)\n",
    "        action_values.append(V[next_pos[0], next_pos[1]])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    best_action = np.argmax(action_values)\n",
    "    obs, reward, done, info = interface.step(best_action)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    img = interface.env.render()\n",
    "    plt.imshow(img)\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"Step {steps+1} | Pos: {env.agent_pos}\")\n",
    "    plt.axis('off')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    steps += 1"
   ]
  }
 ],
